#wrap
  = render("static_pages/navigation.html.haml")
  .container 
    - flash.each do |key,value|
      %div{:class => "alert alert-#{key}"}= value  
    .marketing
      %h2{:style=>'text-align: center'} Let's learn more about your personality
      %br
      %center
        <b>If you already know your type (ex. ENTP):</b>
        = form_tag('/survey' , :method => :post) do
          = label_tag('entered_type', "Personality Type")
          = text_field_tag('entered_type')
          <br>
          = submit_tag("Enter", :class=>"btn btn-primary btn-small") 

      %h4 Otherwise, to get your four character personality "type", we need you to answer the following questions:

      = form_for :input do |f|
        %table.table.table-striped.table-bordered.table-condensed.text1
          %tr
            %th Question
            %th Answer

          %tr.gray1
            %td 1. Groups need people to get things going; and I'm pretty comfortable doing just that:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-1', '1'
              me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-1', '-1'
              not me

          %tr.gray2
            %td 2. When in conversation with people if details are left out:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-1', '1'
              I am eager to have them filled in
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-1', '-1'
              I tend to get the picture without the detail

          %tr.gray1
            %td 3. When I delegate work, I tend to err on this side:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-2', '1'
              Being overly specific
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-2', '-1'
              Being too vague

          %tr.gray2
            %td 4. Which do you tend to be:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-1', '1'
              Tough-minded
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-1', '-1'
              Soft-hearted

          %tr.gray1
            %td 5. When working in a team, group harmony is essential:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-2', '1'
              No
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-2', '-1'
              Yes

          %tr.gray2
            %td 6. You are seldom late:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-1', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-1', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray1
            %td 7. It really bothers you to not have things in their place:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-2', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-2', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray2
            %td 8. I do my best work alone:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-2', '1'
              Not me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-2', '-1'
              Me

          %tr.gray1
            %td 9. When making decisions, I tend to methodically review similar past situations:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-3', '1'
              Me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-3', '-1'
              Not Me

          %tr.gray2
            %td 10. When studying a concept like “leadership” which would you most likely prefer to study:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-4', '1'
              Real life examples
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-4', '-1'
              Ideas and concepts

          %tr.gray1
            %td 11. Being impartial is essential when resolving an issue:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-3', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-3', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray2
            %td 12. In general, you find yourself wishing people would be a little more:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-4', '1'
              Cool and logical
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-4', '-1'
              Warm and caring

          %tr.gray1
            %td 13. You prefer to keep open-ended plans rather than tie events down:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-3', '1'
              No
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-3', '-1'
              Yes

          %tr.gray2
            %td 14. You can trust yourself to improvise more than to plan:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-4', '1'
              No
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-4', '-1'
              Yes

          %tr.gray1
            %td 15. My best ideas and contributions tend to come through lively give-and-take with others:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-3', '1'
              Me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-3', '-1'
              Not Me

          %tr.gray2
            %td 16. What would likely frustrate you more, an approach that is overly:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-5', '1'
              In the clouds
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-5', '-1'
              In the particulars

          %tr.gray1
            %td 17. When meeting someone, do you tend to pay attention to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-6', '1'
              Particular physical characteristics
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-6', '-1'
              The "feel" of who they are

          %tr.gray2
            %td 18. Which way are you more inclined to treat people:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-5', '1'
              Being brutally honest
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-5', '-1'
              Soft-pedaling the hard facts

          %tr.gray1
            %td 19. In study or work decisions I naturally tend to do the things:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-6', '1'
              That move the work along
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-6', '-1'
              That help others work well together

          %tr.gray2
            %td 20. It's just part of your nature to complete your tasks on time:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-5', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-5', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray1
            %td 21. You prefer to make decisions:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-6', '1'
              As soon as practical
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-6', '-1'
              Only when it's all clear

          %tr.gray2
            %td 22. I prefer to share my thanks with:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-4', '1'
              Verbal thanks
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-4', '-1'
              A written note

          %tr.gray1
            %td 23. Facts:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-7', '1'
              speak for themselves
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-7', '-1'
              usually require interpretation

          %tr.gray2
            %td 24. Do you prefer to work with:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-8', '1'
              practical information
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-8', '-1'
              abstract ideas

          %tr.gray1
            %td 25. I prefer a speech that:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-7', '1'
              Informs me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-7', '-1'
              Inspires me

          %tr.gray2
            %td 26. Head over heart:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-8', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-8', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray1
            %td 27. Deadlines are:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-7', '1'
              Almost always real and should be followed
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-7', '-1'
              Useful but not always necessary

          %tr.gray2
            %td 28. You sometimes focus so intently on the goal that you may miss new information:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-8', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-8', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray1
            %td 29. I find working in large groups of people:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-5', '1'
              Energizes me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-5', '-1'
              Tires me out

          %tr.gray2
            %td 30. If you join up with people who have been working in an area for a long time, would you:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-9', '1'
              Assume they know how to do it best
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-9', '-1'
              Keep my eyes open for ways to improve on current systems

          %tr.gray1
            %td 31. Which important work would you prefer:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-10', '1'
              Execute the plan
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-10', '-1'
              Create the plan

          %tr.gray2
            %td 32. I have little patience for personal interest stories and get irritated when other people get swept up in them.:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-9', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-9', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray1
            %td 33. When someone is upset, I tend to want to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-10', '1'
              Understand the underlying issue
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-10', '-1'
              Make sure they feel understood

          %tr.gray2
            %td 34. If you're working, but something really interesting comes along, you're likely to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-9', '1'
              Keep your focus on your work
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-9', '-1'
              Leave your work for the time being

          %tr.gray1
            %td 35. Which appeals to you more to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-10', '1'
              Focus and finish
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-10', '-1'
              Create and adapt

          %tr.gray2
            %td 36. I like to stay connected to a large group of friends as opposed to a few:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-6', '1'
              Me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-6', '-1'
              Not me

          %tr.gray1
            %td 37. Which do you find a more natural way of seeing how things work:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-11', '1'
              Hands-on
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-11', '-1'
              From the balcony

          %tr.gray2
            %td 38. Which would you be more inclined to do in planning:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-12', '1'
              Look at specific situations that could occur and plan for them
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-12', '-1'
              Focus in on the core idea of your strategy

          %tr.gray1
            %td 39. I put others' needs before my own:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-11', '1'
              When it makes sense
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-11', '-1'
              If it will make them feel better

          %tr.gray2
            %td 40. People are amazingly different. So it helps to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-12', '1'
              Have clear, reasonable rules so they can all get along
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-12', '-1'
              Have tons of leeway for individual difference

          %tr.gray1
            %td 41. You make "to-do" lists because:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-11', '1'
              You just love having lists and finishing things
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-11', '-1'
              Without them you know you might not finish things

          %tr.gray2
            %td 42. When you're still working right up to the deadline you tend to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-12', '1'
              Be frustrated that you didn't finish sooner
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-12', '-1'
              Find it pretty typical and feel energized by the pressure

          %tr.gray1
            %td 43. After a long week I prefer to spend Friday night at home with a few friends or alone:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-7', '1'
              Not me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-7', '-1'
              Me

          %tr.gray2
            %td 44. In a group project which job are you more likely to want to take on?
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-13', '1'
              Assembling the final project
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-13', '-1'
              Coming up with the big picture concept

          %tr.gray1
            %td 45. Which seems like a more appealing way to look at a big paper:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-14', '1'
              Create a thorough outline
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-14', '-1'
              Identify the 3 big ideas

          %tr.gray2
            %td 46. If I had to fire someone it's most important that:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-13', '1'
              They understand why
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-13', '-1'
              They feel cared about

          %tr.gray1
            %td 47. In general I prefer to be:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-14', '1'
              Fair
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-14', '-1'
              Understanding

          %tr.gray2
            %td 48. When someone is telling you a story, you tend to 
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-13', '1'
              Need to get to the end result
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-13', '-1'
              Feel no great need to get to the end

          %tr.gray1
            %td 49. You find it very easy to change plans mid-stream:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-14', '1'
              False
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-14', '-1'
              True

          %tr.gray2
            %td 50. I am able to work in distracting and busy environments:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-8', '1'
              Me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-8', '-1'
              Not me

          %tr.gray1
            %td 51. Which are you most comfortable trusting, your:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-15', '1'
              Experience
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-15', '-1'
              Intuition

          %tr.gray2
            %td 52. If you had to quickly assess the suitability of an apartment to rent, would you more likely see if it:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-16', '1'
              Meets your specific requirements
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-16', '-1'
              Just feels right

          %tr.gray1
            %td 53. People say I am too analytical about things:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-15', '1'
              Yes
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-15', '-1'
              No

          %tr.gray2
            %td 54. People say I need to stop worrying about others so much:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-16', '1'
              No
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-16', '-1'
              Yes

          %tr.gray1
            %td 55. I derive pleasure from organizing my life:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-15', '1'
              True
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-15', '-1'
              False

          %tr.gray2
            %td 56. When something unexpected happens your natural tendency is to:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-16', '1'
              Act
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-16', '-1'
              Wait and watch

          %tr.gray1
            %td 57. At a social gathering my conversations tend to be:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-9', '1'
              Numerous and varied
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-9', '-1'
              Few and in depth

          %tr.gray2
            %td 58. How would you more likely be described:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-17', '1'
              Realistic
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-17', '-1'
              Imaginative

          %tr.gray1
            %td 59. Which appeals to you more:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-18', '1'
              Building
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-18', '-1'
              Designing

          %tr.gray2
            %td 60. People who know me well, are more likely to come to me for:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-17', '1'
              Solutions
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-17', '-1'
              Caring

          %tr.gray1
            %td 61. I am one of the first people a friend goes to when seeking consolation or sympathy:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'TF-18', '1'
              No
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'TF-18', '-1'
              Yes

          %tr.gray2
            %td 62. The idea of having a plan on vacation is:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-17', '1'
              Comforting
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-17', '-1'
              Odd

          %tr.gray1
            %td 63. In the long run, what's better for a team working on a project:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'JP-18', '1'
              Excellent results
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'JP-18', '-1'
              Excellent process

          %tr.gray2
            %td 64. I often let calls go to voicemail because I don't feel like talking:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'EI-10', '1'
              Not me
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'EI-10', '-1'
              Me

          %tr.gray1
            %td 65. With a set of Tinkertoys (varied shaped and colored toys to assemble), which would you be more likely to do first:
            %td
              = f.radio_button 'SN-19', '1'
              Sort the pieces in like groups
              %br
              = f.radio_button 'SN-19', '-1'
